  "response_text": "A middle-aged dad with glasses, a short beard, and a light blue button-up shirt kneels on the wooden floor of a busy living room, surrounded by children’s clothes and household clutter. He has both hands on small garments laid out in front of him, as if sorting laundry. The room looks lived-in and family-centered: a couch sits to one side, toys and blankets are scattered around, and a dollhouse is visible in the foreground. In the background, children move around near a dining table in a sunny adjoining room.\n\nThe scene shifts to a bright bathroom or washroom with green walls, white cabinets, and a strip of blue-and-green tile above the sink. Three young girls cluster closely together by the counter. One girl in a yellow shirt stands between the others while they focus on her, holding markers or similar objects. Her face is covered in colorful scribbles and smears—red, green, and dark marks across her cheeks, forehead, chin, and neck. She laughs with her head tilted back while another child’s hand continues marking near her face, making the mess look playful and chaotic.\n\nIn a sunlit room near large windows, the children continue making messes. A red-haired girl in a sleeveless blue-and-white striped dress stands in the background holding a spoon, with a large brown stain spread down the front of her dress. Other children are partially visible in the foreground and to the side, moving around the table area. The girl with the stained striped dress appears to step away as another child in a yellow top turns, holding a pink object in her hand.\n\nThe dad is then shown in a narrow, bright laundry or mudroom with windows on one side and white doors and shelves behind him. An orange bottle of Tide detergent sits prominently on a surface to his left. He holds the blue-and-white striped dress in one hand and a small blue-and-gray cap-like applicator in the other. The cap has a bright blue underside covered with short scrubby bristles and a yellow band around it. He brings the scrubby cap down onto the stained fabric and rubs it directly over the dark mark, treating the dress by hand.\n\nAs he scrubs, a young red-haired girl appears beside him, peeking up from behind the counter near the Tide bottle. Her face is painted pale gray-white with dark eyes and dark lips, giving her a theatrical zombie or monster-like look. She smiles and watches him work, resting a hand near the orange detergent bottle. The dad continues rubbing the fabric, then turns his head toward her. She slips out of view, and he looks after her, pausing with a slightly wary, resigned expression.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean white product display. Two orange Tide bottles stand side by side, one slightly behind the other. The front bottle has a blue cap and a label reading Tide Ultra Stain Release, while the bottle behind it has a darker cap and the classic Tide logo. Large orange and blue text to the right reads, “HELPS REMOVE 99% OF EVERYDAY STAINS,” with “99%” emphasized in blue. Beneath the bottles is “TIDE.COM.” A black paint-stroke graphic then appears over the lower right area with the seasonal-looking words “HAPPY HALLOWCLEAN,” linking the messy, costume-like child imagery to the cleaning message.",
